      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, your symptoms sound like a mild allergic reaction, likely due to pollen. An antihistamine should help alleviate your symptoms. If you don't have any known allergies, you could try taking an antihistamine like diphenhydramine (Benadryl) at a dose of 25-50 mg every 4-6 hours as needed. If symptoms persist or worsen, you may want to consider a short course of a non-drowsy antihistamine like loratadine (Claritin) or fexofenadine (Allegra). But remember, if you start feeling worse, it's always best to consult a doctor.",
